### Basic Markdown Syntax

autosnippet fcb Fenced code block
	\`\`\`${1}
	\`\`\`

snippet sh Fenced code block (sh)
	\`\`\`sh
	${1}
	\`\`\`

snippet typst Fenced code block (typst)
	\`\`\`typst
	${1}
	\`\`\`

snippet c Add Comment
	[//]: # "${1}"

snippet fn Footnote
	[^1]
	[^1]: ${1:Footnote}


### Extended Markdown Support

snippet mermaid Add mermaid flowchart
	\`\`\`mermaid {caption="${1:Every Process a Nike}"}
	---
	config:
	  theme: neutral
	  flowchart:
	    htmlLabels: false
	---
	flowchart LR
	    START(Start) --> DOIT[Just Do It] --> END(End)
	\`\`\`



### Pandoc Typst Support

snippet yaml_frontmatter Yaml Frontmatter #ptp
	---
	title: ${1:title}
	template: ${2:rch.typ}
	date: date${3}
	keywords:
		- A802
	filters:
	- pandoc-internal-link/0.1.0/internal-link.lua
	- pandoc-link-footnote/0.1.0/link-footnote.lua
	- pagebreak.lua
	- pandoc-table-figure/0.1.0/table-figure.lua
	- pandoc-acronyms/0.1.0/acronyms.lua
	- pandoc-diagram/main/diagram.lua
	---

snippet template_doc doc template #ptp
	---
	title: ${1:Title}
	contractor: Red Cedar Consultancy
	contractor_url: www.redcedarconsultancy.com
	template: doc.typ
	keywords: ${2:keywords}
	color: true
	filters:
	- pandoc-internal-link/0.1.0/internal-link.lua
	- pandoc-link-footnote/0.1.0/link-footnote.lua
	- pagebreak.lua
	- pandoc-table-figure/0.1.0/table-figure.lua
	- pandoc-acronyms/0.1.0/acronyms.lua
	- pandoc-diagram/main/diagram.lua
	---

snippet template_sfnet sfnet template
	---
	title: ${1:Title}
	footer_title: ${2:Subtitle}
	template: rch_sfnet.typ
	toc: true
	keywords:
	- headlamp
	filters:
	- pandoc-internal-link/0.1.0/internal-link.lua
	- pandoc-link-footnote/0.1.0/link-footnote.lua
	- pagebreak.lua
	- pandoc-table-figure/0.1.0/table-figure.lua
	- pandoc-acronyms/0.1.0/acronyms.lua
	- pandoc-diagram/main/diagram.lua
	---

snippet filter_pagebreak Filter Config: Pagebreak
	filters:
		- pagebreak.lua
snippet filter_link_footnote Filter Config: Link Footnote
	filters:
		- pandoc-link-footnote/0.1.0/link-footnote.lua
snippet filter_internal_link Filter Config: Internal Link
	filters:
		- pandoc-internal-link/0.1.0/internal-link.lua
snippet filter_acronyms Filter Config: Acronyms
	filters:
		- pandoc-acronyms/0.1.0/acronyms.lua
snippet filter_table_figure Filter Config: Table Figure
	filters:
		- pandoc-table-figure/0.1.0/figure.lua
snippet filter_wordjoin Filter Config: Word Join
	words:
		- BCS-T
		- CS/SCOI
	filters:
		- wordjoin.lua
snippet filter_kbd Filter Config: Keyboard Keys
	filters:
		- pandoc-kbd/0.1.0/kbd.lua

snippet pb Pagebreak
	\pagebreak
snippet internal_link Internal Link
	Jump to the [Introduction](#introduction).
	# Introduction
snippet acronyms Filter Config: Acronyms
	acronyms:
		LAN: Local Area Network
		WAN: Wide Area Network
	filters:
		- pandoc-acronyms/0.1.0/acronyms.lua
snippet table_figure Filter Config: Table Figure
	| First | Last     |
	|-------|----------|
	| John  | Doe      |

	Table:  People I know {#tbl:people}

	See the people I know in +tbl:people.
snippet filter_kbd Filter Config: Keyboard Keys
	To reboot, press +KBD(Ctrl)++KBD(Alt)++KBD(Del).

snippet execute_typst Add Typst code to be processed
	\`\`\`{=typst}
	#heading("Table of Contents", outlined: false, bookmarked:true)
	#outline(title: none)
	#set heading(numbering: "1.1")

	#pagebreak(weak: true)
	\`\`\`


snippet typst_landscape Horizantal page orientation (flipped)
	\`\`\`{=typst}
	#set page(flipped: ${1:true})
	\`\`\`

### Frequently Typed Text

snippet SPP Security Policies and Procedures
	*Security Policies and Procedures* (SPP)
snippet USP Unit Security Plan
	337th ACS *Unit Security Plan* (USP)
snippet EAL Entry Authority List
	*Entry Authority List* (EAL)

snippet NOTE Note Admonition
	> [!NOTE]
	> ${1:Content}

snippet TIP Tip Admonition
	> [!TIP]
	> ${1:Content}

snippet IMPORTANT Important Admonition
	> [!IMPORTANT]
	> ${1:Content}

snippet WARN Warning Admonition
	> [!WARNING]
	> ${1:Content}

snippet CAUTION Caution Admonition
	> [!CAUTION]
	> ${1:Content}
